WEBVTT

00:04.629 --> 00:07.215
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.298 --> 00:10.552
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-own ♪

00:10.635 --> 00:12.011
♪ Outside we
look different ♪

00:12.095 --> 00:13.513
♪ Inside we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.596 --> 00:16.057
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.141 --> 00:18.268
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.351 --> 00:21.479
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-ou ♪

00:21.563 --> 00:23.398
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.481 --> 00:24.899
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:24.983 --> 00:27.444
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:34.826 --> 00:37.287
[ Seth laughs ]

00:37.370 --> 00:38.747
That sounds
just like him!

00:38.830 --> 00:41.332
Do another. Do another,
Sir Tree. Come on.

00:41.416 --> 00:44.419
See if you can guess
this one.

00:44.502 --> 00:48.298
"Oh, hey, I'm the mayor.
Blah blah blah blah.

00:48.381 --> 00:50.091
Here's some laws."

00:50.175 --> 00:52.093
[ Laughs ]

00:52.177 --> 00:53.762
Oh, what a mess.

00:53.845 --> 00:55.430
Leave it to me!

00:58.433 --> 00:59.893
[ Gasps ]
Where'd it go?

00:59.976 --> 01:01.436
It's gone.
The mess.

01:01.519 --> 01:04.397
My roots don't just hold me
in place, Seth.

01:04.481 --> 01:07.525
They absorb water.

01:07.609 --> 01:10.195
It's how I drink.

01:10.278 --> 01:11.321
Whoa.

01:11.404 --> 01:13.531
Can your roots absorb
any liquid?

01:13.615 --> 01:15.116
Let's find out!

01:15.200 --> 01:18.620
♪ Learning all about
my tree friend ♪

01:18.703 --> 01:22.373
♪ My tree friend
is very interesting ♪

01:22.457 --> 01:26.211
♪ I give him things to drink
to see what he will think ♪

01:26.294 --> 01:28.296
♪ I'm not sure what will
make him grow ♪

01:28.379 --> 01:30.256
♪ And what will
make him shrink ♪

01:30.340 --> 01:33.885
♪ Learning all about
my tree friend ♪

01:33.968 --> 01:37.639
♪ My tree friend
is very interesting ♪

01:37.722 --> 01:40.517
♪ Oh yeah ♪

01:40.600 --> 01:41.893
Good news, Sir Tree.

01:41.976 --> 01:43.645
I found this barrel
of oil and --

01:43.728 --> 01:45.230
[ gasps ]

01:45.313 --> 01:47.732
Lay it on me, Seth.

01:47.816 --> 01:49.484
Sir Tree.

01:49.567 --> 01:51.361
You look really sick.

01:51.444 --> 01:54.155
Look, your leaves
are all brittle.

01:54.239 --> 01:57.325
And your skin,
it's all flaky.

01:57.408 --> 01:59.244
I'm fine.

02:01.454 --> 02:04.332
Pour on the oil.

02:04.415 --> 02:06.543
No. No more oil.

02:06.626 --> 02:10.046
I'm calling my mom.

02:10.129 --> 02:11.422
It's okay, Sir Tree!

02:11.506 --> 02:13.258
My doctor mom is here.

02:13.341 --> 02:15.093
It's a party.

02:18.304 --> 02:21.349
I'm not really sure what
temperature a tree should be,

02:21.432 --> 02:22.600
but you know what?

02:22.684 --> 02:24.477
Let's take a look
at these roots.

02:24.561 --> 02:26.896
Don't worry,
I'm a really good doc --

02:26.980 --> 02:28.481
Ahh!

02:28.565 --> 02:29.983
Jeepers!

02:31.943 --> 02:34.696
I mean, I know I'm a doctor,
but gross!

02:34.779 --> 02:36.781
He's got root rot.

02:36.865 --> 02:39.409
Root rot?
This is all my fault.

02:39.492 --> 02:40.869
Hush, now.

02:40.952 --> 02:42.954
I feel fine.

02:44.289 --> 02:45.874
Both: Ew.

02:45.957 --> 02:49.043
Sir Tree needs
some loving care.

02:49.127 --> 02:50.211
Hmmm.

02:50.295 --> 02:53.089
I vow to do everything
in my power

02:53.173 --> 02:56.634
to make Sir Tree
as good as new!

02:56.718 --> 02:58.845
No!
No, no, no!

02:58.928 --> 03:01.222
You've got to take
your fertilizer!

03:01.306 --> 03:03.683
I don't wanna!

03:06.311 --> 03:08.521
Ha! You absorbed
the fertilizer

03:08.605 --> 03:11.900
Nuh-unh.

03:11.983 --> 03:15.361
I'm just trying to get you well.
You know what?

03:15.445 --> 03:19.324
I'm gonna till your soil until
you absorb all this manure!

03:19.407 --> 03:23.286
Oh, a little
termite friend.

03:23.369 --> 03:26.247
Go ahead.
Have a bite of me.

03:26.331 --> 03:28.917
Yeah, bet you like that,
roots, huh?

03:29.000 --> 03:30.335
[ Gasps ]

03:30.418 --> 03:31.628
Sir Tree!

03:31.711 --> 03:33.046
A termite?

03:33.129 --> 03:35.340
That's no way
to treat a guest.

03:35.423 --> 03:37.091
Scoop out a little bit
of my head,

03:37.175 --> 03:39.427
and make a to-go bag
for him.

03:39.510 --> 03:41.930
You can't let bugs eat you
when you're sick.

03:42.013 --> 03:44.641
Being sick is no fun.

03:46.935 --> 03:50.396
If Sir Tree's spirits don't
rise, he'll never get better.

03:51.731 --> 03:54.108
What would make him
feel better?

03:54.192 --> 03:56.027
[ Gasps ]

03:56.110 --> 03:57.153
Sir Tree!

03:57.236 --> 03:59.781
I hereby grant you
one wish!

03:59.864 --> 04:01.616
[ Gasps ]
A wish?

04:01.699 --> 04:03.368
Yeah. Anything.

04:03.451 --> 04:07.121
Well...there is one thing.

04:07.205 --> 04:10.583
Stick 'em up!
This is a robbery!

04:10.667 --> 04:11.876
Oh, no!

04:11.960 --> 04:14.045
It's Nasty Nancy!

04:14.128 --> 04:15.296
A robbery?

04:15.380 --> 04:17.173
Yeah, you heard me.

04:17.257 --> 04:19.384
Put the money
in the bag.

04:19.467 --> 04:21.886
Yes, Mommy --
I mean, ma'am.

04:23.471 --> 04:25.306
Aww, thank you, baby.

04:25.390 --> 04:27.767
I just came here
to make a deposit,

04:27.850 --> 04:30.311
but that doesn't mean
I won't live out

04:30.395 --> 04:34.023
my wildest dream
of catching a bank robber.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.901
You'll have to
catch me first.

04:36.985 --> 04:38.152
Seth:
Set change, everyone.

04:38.236 --> 04:40.989
Ohhh, just try
and catch me, tree!

04:41.072 --> 04:43.491
Sir Tree: Get back here,
Nasty Nancy!

04:43.574 --> 04:45.201
Get back here!

04:45.284 --> 04:46.661
I'm gonna catch you!

04:46.744 --> 04:48.371
Never!

04:50.206 --> 04:53.001
I'm running super fast!

04:53.084 --> 04:54.502
Oh, no!

04:54.585 --> 04:56.796
Oh, look, you're
catching up to me!

04:56.879 --> 04:58.006
Yeah, I am!

04:58.089 --> 04:59.841
I am
catching up to you!

04:59.924 --> 05:01.592
Ohhhh!

05:01.676 --> 05:03.302
You tackled me!

05:03.386 --> 05:05.013
Oof!

05:05.096 --> 05:06.764
Citizen's arrest!

05:06.848 --> 05:09.058
Arrested by a tree.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.476
Did you like
your wish?

05:10.560 --> 05:13.396
What a story to tell
my grandchildren.

05:13.479 --> 05:15.356
And now, rest.

05:15.440 --> 05:19.861
Maybe getting taken care of
isn't so bad after all.

05:19.944 --> 05:27.660
♪♪

05:27.744 --> 05:35.501
♪♪

05:35.585 --> 05:43.217
♪♪

05:43.301 --> 05:45.303
I love being sick.

05:45.386 --> 05:47.221
Seth taking care of me.

05:47.305 --> 05:50.892
I feel like
a little baby.

05:50.975 --> 05:53.352
My leaves grew back?

05:53.436 --> 05:56.189
Oh, no.
My roots look healthy, too.

05:56.272 --> 05:57.940
But if I'm all better,
then --

05:58.024 --> 06:02.945
then Seth won't take care
of me anymore.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.947
I think I am
still sick.

06:05.031 --> 06:08.367
Yeah, these leaves are bad.
These are bad leaves.

06:15.792 --> 06:17.502
And that's why
the Fungie body

06:17.585 --> 06:21.172
needs between 8 to 12
hours of sleep per day.

06:21.255 --> 06:23.424
Oh, nevermind,
it's too much math.

06:23.508 --> 06:24.967
[ Phone rings ]
Huh?

06:31.182 --> 06:33.434
Sir Tree:<i> Oh, hey, Seth.</i>
<i>It's Sir Tree --</i>

06:33.518 --> 06:36.854
you know, your friend
whose roots ya poisoned?

06:36.938 --> 06:39.440
Could you bring me
some comic books?

06:39.524 --> 06:40.858
<i>Could you actually</i>
<i>read them first,</i>

06:40.942 --> 06:42.443
<i>and then,</i>
<i>if there's scary parts,</i>

06:42.527 --> 06:44.112
<i>just cut those out...</i>

06:44.195 --> 06:45.696
Cut out
scary parts.

06:45.780 --> 06:48.324
<i>And set them aside,</i>
<i>and then I can read them later.</i>

06:48.407 --> 06:49.784
[ Clears throat ]

06:49.867 --> 06:52.662
Seth, will you be joining us
for class this morning?

06:55.873 --> 06:58.543
No shellphones
in class, Seth.

06:58.626 --> 06:59.961
Gotta snip them all.

07:00.044 --> 07:04.632
Gotta snip out all the
scary parts for Sir Tree.

07:04.715 --> 07:07.510
Snippy snippy snip snip
snip out all the sc --

07:07.593 --> 07:08.386
Ah!

07:08.469 --> 07:09.679
Oops.
Oh, my gosh.

07:09.762 --> 07:12.723
Hey, how about let's play
some fungieball?

07:12.807 --> 07:14.350
No!
Sir Tree is sick!

07:14.433 --> 07:16.686
He's sick!
Don't you get it?

07:16.769 --> 07:18.146
Uh...yeah.

07:18.229 --> 07:21.065
He needs my comics --
but without the scary parts.

07:21.149 --> 07:22.567
I don't want him
to get more sick.

07:22.650 --> 07:23.818
He's sick!

07:23.901 --> 07:26.654
Well...if you want to play
some fungieball,

07:26.737 --> 07:28.281
you know where
to find us.

07:28.364 --> 07:30.616
Ugh!
I'm so tired.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.827
I feel like I'm
Ms. Electrovolt that one time

07:32.910 --> 07:34.871
she got crushed
under a big...

07:34.954 --> 07:38.958
What??
A healthy leaf?

07:39.041 --> 07:40.168
[ Gasps ]

07:40.251 --> 07:41.669
Sir Tree must be
sicker than ever!

07:41.752 --> 07:44.005
[ Panting ]

07:46.007 --> 07:48.718
That'll make me look
plenty sick.

07:51.304 --> 07:53.181
Oh. Hi, Seth!

07:53.264 --> 07:56.309
Yeah, can't wait to read
these with you, buddy.

07:56.392 --> 07:57.685
Uh, Seth?

07:57.768 --> 07:59.187
See you later, faker.

07:59.270 --> 08:03.191
Cut out your own scary parts,
and sing your own lullabies.

08:03.274 --> 08:04.692
Seth?

08:04.775 --> 08:06.360
I can't believe
that guy.

08:06.444 --> 08:08.529
[ Phone rings]

08:08.613 --> 08:10.364
What?
-Did you...

08:10.448 --> 08:12.408
did you forget something,
and maybe you had to

08:12.491 --> 08:14.368
run back to town?
I don't -- I don't know.

08:14.452 --> 08:15.953
Seth?
Seth?

08:16.037 --> 08:17.330
No.

08:20.333 --> 08:23.377
Oh, hi. You want to
give me a massage?

08:23.461 --> 08:27.256
Oh, look,
another friend!

08:27.340 --> 08:29.383
Lots of friends.

08:29.467 --> 08:31.219
Seth?
Seth?

08:31.302 --> 08:33.888
Aahh!

08:33.971 --> 08:35.723
It's time I make a lunch
for Seth

08:35.806 --> 08:37.934
instead of that sneaky
Sir Tree.

08:38.017 --> 08:40.019
"Would you like
a rock sandwich, Seth?"

08:40.102 --> 08:43.481
"Why thank you, Seth.
That's so polite."

08:43.564 --> 08:45.691
Hey, where's my
water bottle?

08:45.775 --> 08:48.277
Mom!
Where's my...

08:48.361 --> 08:50.071
[ Gasps ]

08:50.154 --> 08:52.323
More tea?

08:52.406 --> 08:54.075
[ Groans ]

08:54.158 --> 08:55.952
I'm just here for the water
bottle, Sir Tree.

08:56.035 --> 08:58.412
Don't you dare think
we're friends again.

08:58.496 --> 08:59.664
[ Gasps ]

08:59.747 --> 09:02.416
Hi, Seth.

09:02.500 --> 09:03.918
What happened?

09:04.001 --> 09:10.049
The universe is punishing me
for being a dirty liar.

09:10.132 --> 09:11.801
I'm fine, Seth.

09:11.884 --> 09:13.511
I don't want to
be a bother.

09:13.594 --> 09:16.764
It's not a bother to help you
when you really need it.

09:19.100 --> 09:21.018
Lil' Seth
to the rescue.

09:21.102 --> 09:22.937
Aww, so cu--

09:24.730 --> 09:26.565
Be careful in there.

09:26.649 --> 09:29.568
It's dangerous
inside my noggin.

09:32.530 --> 09:34.365
Take that!
And that!

09:34.448 --> 09:37.076
And how 'bout
a couple of these!

09:37.159 --> 09:38.828
I'm sorry, Seth.

09:38.911 --> 09:41.622
I just enjoyed
the attention.

09:41.706 --> 09:43.040
It's okay.

09:44.959 --> 09:46.335
I understand.

09:48.045 --> 09:49.463
Ow!

09:51.424 --> 09:54.552
Being sick can make people
not act like themselves.

09:59.265 --> 10:00.433
Hold on a sec.

10:00.516 --> 10:01.851
Let me just finish
these guys off.

10:01.934 --> 10:04.645
It's just you and me,
now, string bean.

10:13.154 --> 10:15.948
Geez!
Abs of steel.

10:18.409 --> 10:19.660
Stop! Wait!

10:19.744 --> 10:22.079
Ahh!

10:22.163 --> 10:24.332
Seth!

10:24.415 --> 10:25.916
Sir Tree! Help!

10:26.000 --> 10:27.460
Hold on!

10:30.713 --> 10:32.089
Victory.

10:32.173 --> 10:35.968
Sir Tree,
I can't hold on much longer.

10:36.052 --> 10:37.219
Ahh!

10:37.303 --> 10:38.929
Seth, NO!

10:39.013 --> 10:39.889
Oh.

10:39.972 --> 10:42.016
Hey, there,
short stuff.

10:42.099 --> 10:44.810
Don't scare me like that,
Sir Tree.

10:44.894 --> 10:46.020
Oh, Seth.

10:46.103 --> 10:47.855
Thank you
for taking care of me.

10:47.938 --> 10:49.774
Sure.
How --

10:49.857 --> 10:51.025
How do you feel?

10:51.108 --> 10:54.570
I feel fine.

10:54.653 --> 10:55.863
Oh.

10:55.946 --> 10:59.241
Well, maybe you could stay
another 10 minutes

10:59.325 --> 11:01.869
while I
collect myself?

11:01.952 --> 11:03.204
I'd love to.

11:03.287 --> 11:05.206
You're a good kid, Seth.

11:05.289 --> 11:11.587
♪♪

11:11.670 --> 11:17.968
♪♪

11:18.052 --> 11:19.637
Oh, what a mess.
